BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Cw7QnjS99PPL83Hffl2cI
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260308T080000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-08T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cGnYLziJByV2fpTNY_g89
SUMMARY:Woodinville Half
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260308T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Kirk-Wood Half is now the Woodinville Half Hello runners\, We k
	now many of you have been looking forward to the Kirk-Wood Half Marathon\,
	 and we appreciate your understanding as we share an important update rega
	rding the event. Unfortunately\, we have had to change the route for the K
	irk-Wood Half due to ongoing construction on the Kirkland Cross Corridor T
	rail.  The good news: the half marathon will still take place on Sunday\, 
	March 8 — just with an updated route. The event will now start and finish 
	at Wilmot Park\, which was originally planned as the finish line. This eli
	minates the need for participant shuttles and allows us to offer a flat\, 
	fast\, and fun course. We are incredibly grateful for the support and flex
	ibility shown by the City of Woodinville and King County Parks in making t
	his possible. At this time\, our focus is on delivering an exceptional rac
	e experience on March 8. The City of Kirkland has indicated a willingness 
	to permit the event on a future date\, and we are exploring the possibilit
	y of hosting the Kirk-Wood Half Marathon later this year. Important Update
	s: The event will now be called the Woodinville Half Marathon. All partici
	pants will receive a free slice of pizza from The Pizza Coup post-race  . 
	All participants will still receive a full-zip hooded sweatshirt with regi
	stration. We will be updating the design. View the new course map: https:/
	/www.mapmyrun.com/routes/view/6667331427 Thank you for your continued supp
	ort\, we can’t wait to see you at the start line! Sincerely\, Grant Harrin
	gton Owner Snohomish Running Company\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/event
	s/#/details/woodinville-half/18291053/2026-03-08T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/woodinville-half/18291053
	/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Kirkland Marina Park\, 25 Lakeshore Plz Dr\, Kirkland\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MKK7UEJDlxZ5dajHflunx
SUMMARY:WA Concealed Carry Class at Wildlife Committee of
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260308T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 4-hour comprehensive training course is designed to educat
	e individuals on the laws and regulations surrounding the carrying of conc
	ealed firearms. This class covers essential topics such as the use of forc
	e\, firearms safety\, and the proper handling and storage of firearms\, as
	 well as the specific laws and any requirements for obtaining permits in W
	ashington\, Oregon\, Arizona\, and Utah. Upon completion of the class\, at
	tendees will be eligible to apply for the above-mentioned permits. You wil
	l also receive a WA - HB-1143 Gun Safety Certificate. DATES and TIMES are 
	subject to change\, please view our website for the most up to date and ac
	curate class info. https://www.legalheat.com/classes/in-person/concealed-c
	arry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of-washington-bothell-wa/?utm\\_source=fa
	cebook&utm\\_medium=event\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details
	/wa-concealed-carry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wa-concealed-carry-class-
	at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Wildlife Committee of Washington - WCWShootingSports - Kenmore Ran
	ge\, 1031 228th St SW\, Bothell\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zVZMd6WL8b-vSVvdyDRpH
SUMMARY:Sermon Series: 1 Peter
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260308T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:This winter\, from January to Easter\, we are walking through 1
	 Peter at Woodmark Church. Some of you know the book well. For others\, it
	 may feel unfamiliar. But Peter names the tension every believer feels. We
	 live in a world that often moves in a different direction. He calls us “e
	xiles\,” yet reminds us we are chosen\, loved\, held by a living hope. The
	 heart of this series is simple. It is not just about studying a letter. I
	t is about becoming the kind of people Peter envisions: Steady. Courageous
	. Formed by grace. Join us each Sunday\, 9:30 am and 11:30 am in Kirkland.
	\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sermon-series-1-peter/18
	291158/2026-03-08T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sermon-series-1-peter/182
	91158/2026-03-08T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H30M
END:VEVENT
