UID:4HvZdqZCH9iGfDHJPj9Tj
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260313T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.c
	om/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we-leave-behind/18026187/2026-0
	3-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-03-13T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Y_C37wHMsFv5G0-H9iTjk
SUMMARY:Lichen Walk
DTSTAMP:20260307T234429Z
DTSTART:20260313T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Dr. Katherine Glew. Have you always wondered what lic
	hens are and why they are found on your trees\, rhododendrons and azaleas?
	 Lichens are harmless to your plants and add aesthetic value to your garde
	n. Learn about common lichens found in an urban environment and what they 
	tell us about air quality\, forest health\, geology and why they are indic
	ators of changes in the climate\, ecosystems\, and geology. You will leave
	 with a fresh understanding about lichens and a user-friendly chart that l
	ists lichens found in your neighborhood. This walk will be on trails with 
	various surfaces and may include gravel\, mulch\, or pavement. Please dres
	s for the weather and wear comfortable walking shoes. $28 BBGS members/$40
	 nonmembers.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/lichen-walk/
	17923216/2026-03-13T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/lichen-walk/17923216/2026
	-03-13T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
